gomodel:SYNGO_3033  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.7: \"Subcellular distribution of rHIP1R protein in the rat brain and comparison with that of huntingtin.\"\n- \"The rHIP1R immunoreactive protein of 120 kDa was detected in the total homogenate, P1 (cell debris and nuclei), the synaptosome and the SPM fractions. The rHIP1R-immunoreactive protein was enriched in the SPM fraction and a faint band was detected in the synaptosome fraction, but was not present in the PSD fraction that was obtained after Triton X-100 treatment and Triton X-100-KCl washing of SPM. \"\n\nFig.9: \"Electron microscopic examination of rHIP1R in the rat cerebral cortex\"\n- \"Immunoreactivities were observed in the cytoplasmic structures in the spines including PSDs and structures which were attached or very close to PSD and apart from PSD (Fig. 9).\"\n- \"The presynaptic terminals were constantly negative for staining.\"\n\nNote: the patches in the postsynapse may be the endocytic zone (see PMID:11564758) but this is not demonstrated.. Experimental description: - \"Subcellular fractions of the forebrain were prepared from Wistar rats...\"\n- \" Immunohistochemical examination: Brains from Wistar rats (6 weeks old) w...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3033" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

